  "market_context": "Gold had a strong expansion on the previous 4-hour day and was forming a shallow, non-aggressive retracement back into a 4-hour fair value gap, suggesting continuation higher rather than reversal.",
  "key_observation": "The 4H FVG around 2836–2842 acted as the key POI; after sweeping the low on the 15M, price formed a change in state of delivery and then provided multiple continuation entries off respected order blocks before reaching 2R at the prior high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: On the 4H, identify the prior day's expansion and confirm the retracement is shallow with non-aggressive candles, tagging into a 4H fair value gap.",
    "Step 2: Drop down to the 15M timeframe at the open of the new 4H candle and observe the sweep of the low into the 4H FVG (around 2836–2842).",
    "Step 3: Wait for a change in state of delivery — down-close candles being closed through — noting this also aligns with the opening price, plus another minor sweep of equal lows.",
    "Step 4: Treat the CISD as the first reversal entry; for more confirmation, wait for a continuation by letting price retrace into an important level with an opposing (down-close) candle.",
    "Step 5: Take the continuation entry on the close through the down-close candle into the FVG, stop on the low, target 2R at the previous high.",
    "Step 6: On the retest, identify another down-close candle into the order block at the important level; that low is respected, providing an additional continuation entry.",
    "Step 7: Price trades higher, retests the previous high and completes 2R — the 15-minute Market Maker Buy Model — with all timeframes aligned in one direction."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade reached 2R / previous high, completing the 15-minute Market Maker Buy Model.",
  "lessons": "Aligning the 4H POI (FVG) with a 15M CISD provides a first entry; waiting for opposing candles at important levels gives additional continuation entries with tighter risk. Timeframe alignment is what produces clean expansion.",
